The paper deals with denotational semantics and computational complexity in linear logic, which are topics typically studied in the subfield of logic (cs.LO). The use of coherence spaces and normal functors also suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and category theory (cs.CC). The discussion of cardinality and complexity bounds further supports the relevance to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
